{
  "texts": [
    "For student previous academic features, have only been used in three studies Brdesee et al (2022); Song et al (2020); Yousafzai et al (2021) as these studies have already incorporated all the other categories of features.",
    "The reviewed studies used one, two, or three categories of features when predicting student's academic performance.",
    "Using only one category of features seems to be popular for predicting student's academic performance.",
    "As shown in Figure 16, one feature category was associated with about 41% of the studies.",
    "In all the reviewed articles, 22% of the studies combined three feature categories, whereas 37% combined two different feature categories in their studies, and none of them have used four combinations of feature's groups."
  ]
}